obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (41316)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41316&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Bonded Labour System`
  line `(Abolition) Act, 1976.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 25th day of October, 1975.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (41317)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Explanation added by Act 73 of 1985, s. 2 (w.e.f. 24-12-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41317&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "advance" means an advance, whether in cash or in kind, or partly in cash or partly in kind,`
  line `made by one person (hereinafter referred to as the creditor) to another person (hereinafter referred to`
  line `as the debtor);`
  line
  line `(b) "agreement" means an agreement (whether written or oral, or partly written and partly oral)`
  line `between a debtor and creditor, and includes an agreement providing for forced labour, the existence`
  line `of which is presumed under any social custom prevailing in the concerned locality.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The existence of an agreement between the debtor and creditor is ordinarily`
  line `presumed, under the social custom, in relation to the following forms of forced labour, namely:--`
  line
  line `Adiyamar, Baramasia, Basahya, Bethu, Bhagela, Cherumar, Garru-Galu, Hali, Hari, Harwai,`
  line `Holya, Jana, Jeetha, Kamiya, Khundit-Mundit, Kuthia, Lakhari, Munjhi, Mat, Munish system,`
  line `Nit-Majoor, Paleru, Padiyal, Pannayilal, Sagri, Sanji,Sanjawat, Sewak, Sewakia, Seri, Vetti;`
  line
  line `(c) "ascendant" or "descendant", in relation to a person belonging to a matriarchal society, means`
  line `the person who corresponds to such expression in accordance with the law of succession in force in`
  line `such society;`
  line
  line `(d) "bonded debt" means an advance obtained, or presumed to have been obtained, by a bonded`
  line `labourer under, or in pursuance of, the bonded labour system;`
  line
  line `(e) "bonded labour" means any labour or service rendered under the bonded labour system;`
  line
  line `(f) "bonded labourer" means a labourer who incurs, or has, or is presumed to have, incurred, a`
  line `bonded debt;`
  line
  line `(g) "bonded labour system" means the system of forced, or partly forced, labour under which a`
  line `debtor enters, or has, or is presumed to have, entered, into an agreement with the creditor to the effect`
  line that,--
  line
  line `(i) in consideration of an advance obtained by him or by any of his lineal ascendants or`
  line `descendants (whether or not such advance is evidenced by any document) and in consideration of`
  line `the interest, if any, due on such advance, or`
  line
  line `(ii) in pursuance of any customary or social obligation, or`
  line
  line `(iii) in pursuance of an obligation devolving on him by succession, or`
  line
  line `(iv) for any economic consideration received by him or by any of his lineal ascendants or`
  line `descendants, or`
  line
  line `(v) by reason of his birth in any particular caste or community,`
  line
  line `he would--`
  line
  line `(1) render, by himself or through any member of his family, or any person dependent on him,`
  line `labour or service to the creditor, or for the benefit of the creditor, for a specified period or for an`
  line `unspecified period, either without wages or for nominal wages, or`
  line
  line `(2) forfeit the freedom of employment or other means of livelihood for a specified period or`
  line `for an unspecified period, or`
  line
  line `(3) forfeit the right to move freely throughout the territory of India, or`
  line
  line `(4) forfeit the right to appropriate or sell at market value any of his property or product of his`
  line `labour or the labour of a member of his family or any person dependent on him,`
  line
  line `and includes the system of forced, or partly forced, labour under which a surety for a debtor enters, or`
  line `has, or is presumed to have, entered, into an agreement with the creditor to the effect that in the event`
  line `of the failure of the debtor to repay the debt, he would render the bonded labour on behalf of the`
  line debtor.
  line
  line ^1
  line `[Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that any system of forced, or partly`
  line `forced labour under which any workman being contract labour as defined in clause (b) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 2 of the Contract Labour (Regulation and Abolition) Act, 1970 (37 of 1970), or an inter-State`
  line `migrant workman as defined in clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Inter-State Migrant`
  line `Workmen (Regulation of Employment and Conditions of Service) Act, 1979 (30 of 1979), is required to`
  line `render labour or service in circumstances of the nature mentioned in sub-clause (1) of this clause or is`
  line `subjected to all or any of the disabilities referred to in sub-clauses (2) to (4), is "bonded labour system"`
  line `within the meaning of this clause;]`
  line
  line `(h) "family", in relation to a person, includes the ascendant and descendant of such person;`
  line
  line `(i) "nominal wages", in relation to any labour, means a wage which is less than,--`
  line
  line `(a) the minimum wages fixed by the Government, in relation to the same or similar labour,`
  line `under any law for the time being in force, and`
  line
  line `(b) where no such minimum wage has been fixed in relation to any form of labour, the wages`
  line `that are normally paid, for the same or similar labour, to the labourers working in the same`
  line locality;
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (41318)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41318&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The prvisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any enactment other than this Act, or in any instrument`
  line `having effect by virtue of any enactment other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (41319)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Abolition of bonded labour system.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41319&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the commencement of this Act, the bonded labour`
  line `system shall stand abolished and every bonded labourer shall, on such commencement, stand freed and`
  line `discharged from any obligation to render any bonded labour.`
  line
  line `(2) After the commencement of this Act, no person shall--`
  line
  line `(a) make any advance under, or in pursuance of, the bonded labour system, or`
  line
  line `(b) compel any person to render any bonded labour or other form of forced labour.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (41320)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Agreement, custom, etc., to be void.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41320&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `On the commencement of this Act, any custom or tradition`
  line `or any contract, agreement or other instrument (whether entered into or executed before or after the`
  line `commencement of this Act), by virtue of which any person, or any member of the family or dependant of`
  line `such person, is required to do any work or render any service as a bonded labourer, shall be void and`
  line inoperative.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (41321)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Liability to repay bonded debt to stand extinguished.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41321&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the commencement of this Act,`
  line `every obligation of a bonded labourer to repay any bonded debt, or such part of any bonded debt as`
  line `remains unsatisfied immediately before such commencement, shall be deemed to have been extinguished.`
  line
  line `(2) After the commencement of this Act, no suit or other proceeding shall lie in any civil court or`
  line `before any other authority for the recovery of any bonded debt or any part thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) Every decree or order for the recovery of bonded debt, passed before the commencement of this`
  line `Act and not fully satisfied before such commencement, shall be deemed, on such commencement, to have`
  line `been fully satisfied.`
  line
  line `(4) Every attachment made before the commencement of this Act, for the recovery of any bonded`
  line `debt, shall, on such commencement, stand vacated; and, where, in pursuance of such attachment, any`
  line `movable property of the bonded labourer was seized and removed from his custody and kept in the`
  line `custody of any court or other authority pending sale thereof, such movable property shall be restored, as`
  line `soon as may be practicable after such commencement, to the possession of the bonded labourer.`
  line
  line `(5) Where, before the commencement of this Act, possession of any property belonging to a bonded`
  line `labourer or a member of his family or other dependant was forcibly taken over by any creditor for the`
  line `recovery of any bonded debt, such property shall be restored, as soon as may be practicable after such`
  line `commencement, to the possession of the person from whom it was seized.`
  line
  line `(6) If restoration of the possession of any property referred to in sub-section (4) or sub-section (5) is`
  line `not made within thirty days from the commencement of this Act, the aggrieved person may, within such`
  line `time as may be prescribed, apply to the prescribed authority for the restoration of the possession of such`
  line `property and the prescribed authority may, after giving the creditor a reasonable opportunity of being`
  line `heard, direct the creditor to restore to the applicant the possession of the concerned property within such`
  line `time as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(7) An order made by any prescribed authority, under sub-section (6), shall be deemed to be an order`
  line `made by a civil court and may be executed by the court of the lowest pecuniary jurisdiction within the`
  line `local limits of whose jurisdiction the creditor voluntarily resides or carries on business or personally`
  line `works for gain.`
  line
  line `(8) For the avoidance of doubts, it is hereby declared that, where any attached property was sold`
  line `before the commencement of this Act, in execution of a decree or order for the recovery of a bonded debt,`
  line `such sale shall not be affected by any provision of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the bonded labourer, or an agent authorised by him in this behalf, may, at any time`
  line `within five years from such commencement, apply to have the sale set aside on his depositing in court, for`
  line `payment to the decree-holder, the amount specified in the proclamation of sale, for the recovery of which`
  line `the sale was ordered, less any amount, as well as mesne profits, which may, since the date of such`
  line `proclamation of sale, have been received by the decree-holder.`
  line
  line `(9) Where any suit or proceeding, for the enforcement of any obligation under the bonded labour`
  line `system, including a suit or proceeding for the recovery of any advance made to a bonded labourer, is`
  line `pending at the commencement of this Act, such suit or other proceeding shall, on such commencement,`
  line `stand dismissed.`
  line
  line `(10) On the commencement of this Act, every bonded labourer who has been detained in civil prison,`
  line `whether before or after judgment, shall be released from detention forthwith.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (41322)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Property of bonded labourer to be freed from mortgage, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41322&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) All property vested in a`
  line `bonded labourer which was, immediately before the commencement of this Act under any mortgage,`
  line `charge, lien or other incumbrances in connection with any bonded debt shall, in so far as it is relatable to`
  line `the bonded debt, stand freed and discharged from such mortgage, charge, lien or other incumbrances, and`
  line `where any such property was, immediately before the commmencement of this Act, in the possession of`
  line `the mortgagee or the holder of the charge, lien or incumbrance, such property shall (except where it was`
  line `subject to any other charge), on such commencement, be restored to the possession of the bonded`
  line labourer.
  line
  line `(2) If any delay is made in restoring any property, referred to in sub-section (1), to the possession of`
  line `the bonded labourer, such labourer shall be entitled, on and from the date of such commencement, to`
  line `recover from the mortgagee or holder of the lien, charge or incumbrance, such mesne profits as may be`
  line `determined by the civil court of the lowest pecuniary jurisdiction within the local limits of whose`
  line `jurisdiction such property is situated.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (41323)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Freed bonded labourer not to be evicted from homestead, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41323&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person who has been`
  line `freed and discharged under this Act from any obligation to render any bonded labour, shall be evicted`
  line `from any homestead or other residential premises which he was occupying immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act as part of the consideration for the bonded labour.`
  line
  line `(2) If, after the commencement of this Act, any such person is evicted by the creditor from any`
  line `homestead or other residential premises, referred to in sub-section (1), the Executive Magistrate in charge`
  line `of the Sub-Division within which such homestead or residential premises is situated shall, as early as`
  line `practicable, restore the bonded labourer to the possession of such homestead or other residential premises.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (41324)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Creditor not to accept payment against extinguished debt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41324&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) No creditor shall accept any`
  line `payment against any bonded debt which has been extinguished or deemed to have been extinguished or`
  line `fully satisfied by virtue of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) shall be punishable with imprisonment for`
  line `a term which may extend to three years and also with fine.`
  line
  line `(3) The court, convicting any person under sub-section (2) may, in addition to the penalties which`
  line `may be imposed under that sub-section, direct the person to deposit, in court, the amount accepted in`
  line `contravention of the provisions of sub-section (1), within such period as may be specified in the order for`
  line `being refunded to the bonded labourer.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (41325)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Authorities who may be specified for implementing the provisions of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41325&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The State`
  line `Government may confer such powers and impose such duties on a District Magistrate as may be`
  line `necessary to ensure that the provisions of this Act are properly carried out and the District Magistrate may`
  line `specify the officer, subordinate to him, who shall exercise all or any of the powers, and perform all or any`
  line `of the duties, so conferred or imposed and the local limits within which such powers or duties shall be`
  line `carried out by the officer so specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (41326)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Duty of District Magistrate and other officers to ensure credit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41326&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The District Magistrate`
  line `authorised by the State Government under section 10 and the officer specified by the District Magistrate`
  line `under that section shall, as far as practicable, try to promote the welfare of the freed bonded labourer by`
  line `securing and protecting the economic interests of such bonded labourer so that he may not have any`
  line `occasion or reason to contract any further bonded debt.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (41327)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Duty of District Magistrate and officers authorised by him.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41327&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of every`
  line `District Magistrate and every officer specified by him under section 10 to inquire whether, after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, any bonded labour system or any other form of forced labour is being`
  line `enforced by, or on behalf of, any person resident within the local limits of his jurisdiction and if, as a`
  line `result of such inquiry, any person is found to be enorcing the bonded labour system or any other system`
  line `of forced labour, he shall forthwith take such action as may be necessary to eradicate the enforcement of`
  line `such forced labour.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (41328)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Vigilance Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41328&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Government shall, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, constitute such number of Vigilance Committees in each district and each Sub-Division as it may`
  line `think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Each Vigilance Committee, constituted for a district, shall consist of the following members,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the District Magistrate, or a person nominated by him, who shall be the Chairman;`
  line
  line `(b) three persons belonging to the Scheduled Castes or Scheduled Tribes and residing in the`
  line `district, to be nominated by the District Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(c) two social workers, resident in the district, to be nominated by the District Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(d) not more than three persons to represent the official or non-official agencies in the district`
  line `connected with rural development, to be nominated by the State Government;`
  line
  line `(e) one person to represent the financial and credit institutions in the district, to be nominated by`
  line `the District Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(3) Each Vigilance Committee, constituted for a Sub-Division, shall consist of the following`
  line `members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Sub-Divisional Magistrate, or a person nominated by him, who shall be the Chairman;`
  line
  line `(b) three persons belonging to the Scheduled Castes or Scheduled Tribes and residing in the`
  line `Sub-Division, to be nominated by the Sub-Divisional Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(c) two social workers, resident in the Sub-Division, to be nominated by the Sub-Divisional`
  line Magistrate;
  line
  line `(d) not more than three persons to represent the official or non-official agencies in the`
  line `Sub-Division connected with rural development to be nominated by the District Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(e) one person to represent the financial and credit institutions in the Sub-Division, to be`
  line `nominated by the Sub-Divisional Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(f) one officer specified under section 10 and functioning in the Sub-Division.`
  line
  line `(4) Each Vigilance Committee shall regulate its own procedure and secretarial assistance, as may be`
  line `necessary, shall be provided by--`
  line
  line `(a) the District Magistrate, in the case of a Vigilance Committee constituted for the district;`
  line
  line `(b) the Sub-Divisional Magistrate, in the case of a Vigilance Committee constituted for the`
  line Sub-Division.
  line
  line `(5) No proceeding of a Vigilance Committee shall be invalid merely by reason of any defect in the`
  line `constitution, or in the proceedings, of the Vigilance Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (41329)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Functions of Vigilance Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41329&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The functions of each Vigilance Committee shall`
  line be,--
  line
  line `(a) to advise the District Magistrate or any officer authorised by him as to the efforts made, and`
  line `action taken, to ensure that the provisions of this Act or of any rule made thereunder are properly`
  line implemented;
  line
  line `(b) to provide for the economic and social rehabilitation of the freed bonded labourers;`
  line
  line `(c) to co-ordinate the functions of rural banks and co-operative societies with a view to canalising`
  line `adequate credit to the freed bonded labourer;`
  line
  line `(d) to keep an eye on the number of offences of which cognizance has been taken under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) to make a survey as to whether there is any offence of which cognizance ought to be taken under`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) to defend any suit instituted against a freed bonded labourer or a member of his family or any`
  line `other person dependant on him for the recovery of the whole or part of any bonded debt or any other debt`
  line `which is claimed by such person to be bonded debt.`
  line
  line `(2) A Vigilance Committee may authorise one of its members to defend a suit against a freed bonded`
  line `labourer and the member so authorised shall be deemed, for the purpose of such suit, to be the authorised`
  line `agent of the freed bonded labourer.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (41330)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Burden of proof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41330&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any debt is claimed by a bonded labourer, or a Vigilance`
  line `Committee, to be a bonded debt, the burden of proof that such debt is not a bonded debt shall lie on the`
  line creditor.
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (41331)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Punishment for enforcement of bonded labour.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41331&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, after the commencement of this`
  line `Act, compels any person to render any bonded labour shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to three years and also with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (41332)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Punishment for advancement of bonded debt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41332&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Whoever advances, after the commencement`
  line `of this Act, any bonded debt shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three`
  line `years and also with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (41333)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Punishment for extracting bonded labour under the bonded labour system.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41333&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `enforces, after the commencement of this Act, any custom, tradition, contract, agreement or other`
  line `instrument, by virtue of which any person or any member of the family of such person or any dependant`
  line `of such person is required to render any service under the bonded labour system, shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years and also with fine which may extend to two`
  line `thousand rupees; and, out of the fine, if recovered, payment shall be made to the bonded labourer at the`
  line `rate of rupees five for each day for which the bonded labour was extracted from him.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (41334)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Punishment for omission or failure to restore possession of property to bonded labourers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41334&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being required by this Act to restore any property to the possession of any bonded`
  line `labourer, omits or fails to do so, within a period of thirty days from the commencement of this Act, shall`
  line `be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to one thousand rupees, or with both; and, out of the fine, if recovered, payment shall be made to`
  line `the bonded labourer at the rate of rupees five for each day during which possession of the property was`
  line `not restored to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (41335)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Abetment to be an offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41335&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Whoever abets any offence punishable under this Act shall,`
  line `whether or not the offence abetted is committed, be punishable with the same punishment as is provided`
  line `for the offence which has been abetted.`
  line
  line `Explanation,--For the purpose of this Act, "abetment" has the meaning assigned to it in the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (41336)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Offences to be tried by Executive Magistrates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41336&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may confer, on`
  line `an Executive Magistrate, the powers of a Judicial Magistrate of the first class or of the second class`
  line `for the trial of offences under this Act; and, on such conferment of powers, the Executive Magistate,`
  line `on whom the powers are so conferred, shall be deemed, for the purposes of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), to be a Judicial Magistrate of the first class, or of the second class, as the`
  line `case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) An offence under this Act may be tried summarily by a Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (41337)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content `Every offence under this Act shall be cognizable and bailable.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41337&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (41338)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41338&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to, any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director" , in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (41339)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41339&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against any State Government or any officer of the State Government or any member of the Vigilance`
  line `Committee for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (41340)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Jurisdiction of civil courts barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41340&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction in respect of any`
  line `matter to which any provision of this Act applies and no injunction shall be granted by any civil court in`
  line `respect of anything which is done or intended to be done by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (41341)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41341&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all or any`
  line `of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the authority to which application for the restoration of possession of property referred to in`
  line `sub-section (4), or sub-section (5), of section 6 is to be submitted in pursuance of sub-section (6) of`
  line `that section;`
  line
  line `(b) the time within which application for restoration of possession of property is to be made,`
  line `under sub-section (6) of section 6, to the prescribed authority;`
  line
  line `(c) steps to be taken by Vigilance Committees under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 14, to`
  line `ensure the implementation of the provisions of this Act or of any rule made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may`
  line `be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (41342)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694&sectionId=41342&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00006_197619_1517807318694
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bonded Labour System (Abolition) Ordinance, 1975 (17 of 1975)`
  line `is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the Ordinance (including`
  line `any notification published, direction or nomination made, power conferred, duty imposed or officer`
  line `specified) shall be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
